abstract: 'This interactive textbook provides learning content for all aspects related to the use of lead isotopes in archaeological research, particularly the reconstruction of the raw material provenance. It combines aspects of geochemistry, archaeology and data science into a holistic approach to this topic. It is an open educational resource, meaning that its content is free and the community is invited to participate in its creation. Read it at <https://archmetaldbm.github.io/GlobaLID-Edu/>'
